org.matsim.contrib.common.randomizedtransitrouter

Class RandomizingTransitRouterTravelTimeAndDisutility

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.pt.router.TransitRouterNetworkTravelTimeAndDisutility
      • org.matsim.contrib.common.randomizedtransitrouter.RandomizingTransitRouterTravelTimeAndDisutility
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MatsimExtensionPoint, TravelTime, TransitTravelDisutility

    public class RandomizingTransitRouterTravelTimeAndDisutility
extends TransitRouterNetworkTravelTimeAndDisutility
    When plugged into the transit router, will switch to a different, randomly generated combination of marginal utilities every time it is called for a new agent.

    Comments:
    • In the literature, they seem to use log-normal distributions for the tastes. (Makes sense since it addresse the symmetry problem which I am addressing ad-hoc.) [M. K. Anderson, hEART'13] kai, sep'13
    • People seem to use "gamma distributions for the error term" ("double stochastic assignment"). Not sure what that does, if we need it, etc. [M. K. Anderson, hEART'13] kai, sep'13
    Author:
    kai, dgrether
